:"\nThe left side of a let-expression allows you to pattern match on values to assign them to variables, but also to deconstruct them and access their inner values.\n\n   ```ocaml\n   let variable = 42 in\n   let { x; _ } = point in\n   let Some x = optional in\n   (* ... *)\n   ```\n\nBeware that pattern matching on only one of many possible values will lead to runtime errors!\n"},"span":{"start":22,"end":22}},{"kind":{"id":"E0008","name":"invalid-expression","expected":"expression","found":{"kind":"`","text":"`"},"hint":"Expected a value, function call, or operator expression."},"span":{"start":22,"end":22}},{"kind":{"id":"E0008","name":"invalid-expression","expected":"expression","found":{"kind":"`","text":"`"},"hint":"Expected a value, function call, or operator expression."},"span":{"start":24,"end":28}},{"kind":{"id":"E0005","name":"unexpected-structure-item","expected":"structure item (e.g., let, type, module)","found":{"kind":"keyword","text":"as"},"hint":"Structure items are top-level declarations like let, type, or module."},"span":{"start":33,"end":34}},{"kind":{"id":"E0005","name":"unexpected-structure-item","expected":"structure item (e.g., let, type, module)","found":{"kind":"identifier","text":"v"},"hint":"Structure items are top-level declarations like let, type, or module."},"span":{"start":35,"end":36}},{"kind":{"id":"E0005","name":"unexpected-structure-item","expected":"structure item (e.g., let, type, module)","found":{"kind":"->","text":"->"},"hint":"Structure items are top-level declarations like let, type, or module."},"span":{"start":38,"end":39}},{"kind":{"id":"E0005","name":"unexpected-structure-item","expected":"structure item (e.g., let, type, module)","found":{"kind":"identifier","text":"v"},"hint":"Structure items are top-level declarations like let, type, or module."},"span":{"start":40,"end":41}},{"kind":{"id":"E0005","name":"unexpected-structure-item","expected":"structure item (e.g., let, type, module)","found":{"kind":"|","text":"|